gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 121, Clippers 100
gameRecap.excerpt: The Minnesota Timberwolves defeated the Los Angeles Clippers, 121-100. Karl-Anthony Towns led Minnesota with 24 points as Anthony Edwards (23 points, seven rebounds, eight assists) and Rudy Gobert (17 points, 10 rebounds, four blocks) totaled 40 points. Paul George (18 points, six rebounds) and Kawhi Leonard (18 points) led Los Angeles as James Harden added 17 points. The Timberwolves improve to 37-16 as the Clippers move to 35-17.
